    ringsm.1 $e |- G = ( 1st ` R ) $.
    ringsm.2 $e |- H = ( 2nd ` R ) $.
    ringsm.3 $e |- X = ran G $.
    $( Functionality of the multiplication operation of a ring.  (Contributed
       by Steve Rodriguez, 9-Sep-2007.) $)
    ringsm $p |- ( R e. RingOps -> H : ( X X. X ) --> X ) $=
      ( vx vy vz cring wcel cabl cxp wf wa cv co wceq w3a wral wrex ringoi
      simpld simprd ) AKLZBMLZDDNDCOZUFUGUHPHQZIQZCRZJQZCRUIUJULCRZCRSUIUJULBRC
